args:
While struggling through the rugged mountain
path, the prince once again thanks Zena for
encouraging and guiding him to this point.
Suddenly, Ciella appears and discloses
that Elisanne is hiding something before
provoking the party into battle.
*pant* Still alive, at any rate—though\nthis IS a rather precipitous path.
We're skimmin' clouds at this altitude.\nOne slip, and it's a long, bumpy roll\nall the way down the valley.
Yes, everyone be extra careful up here.\nWhat about you, Zena? Are you all right?
Your concern is appreciated,\nbut unnecessary. I am well.
It would not do for me to slow you down\nafter you allowed me to travel with you,\nso I shall make my way on my own two—
I can handle this fiend. Haaaah!
I just... When I saw you being attacked,\nit was like watching it happen to Zethia.
I suppose there is not much to be done\nabout that, all things considered.
I'm glad you don't need my help,\nbut it also makes me a little...\nWell, sad, I guess. Is that silly?
I hope you know I'm not looking at you\nto be some kind of Zethia replacement.
Without your encouragement, I wouldn't\nhave mustered the determination to come\nhere—and I'm truly grateful for that.
Heck yeah! Things have been all kinds of\nbad lately, but havin' you around gives us\nthe strength to keep on keepin' on.
Yep. No matter where yer from,\nit's good to have ya here.
Utterly hopeless, the lot of you.
I had intended to remain hidden, but upon\nhearing your lie-filled conversation,\nI could contain myself no longer.
She's a member of Agito who\nattacked the Ilian Church.
How good to meet you, other Auspex.
I am Ciella, Agito's wings of judgment.\nI have escaped the fraudulent rule of the\nIlian Church and awakened to the truth.
Ah! Greetings once again, Paladyn.\nYour expression is looking rather grim.
First Volk, now you... I knew Agito was\nbehind Zethia's kidnapping!
Will you fools never change? You stare\ninto a pond of infinite depth, yet refuse\nto see anything but the surface.

You are pitiful—and because you all
insist on continuing this insipid charade
of friendship, you have lost the ability
to see the truth.
Hey, this is NOT a charade, sister!\nI love everybody here!
Perhaps you are simply jealous because\nyou have no friends of your own.

Your bonds are superficial; you tiptoe
about each other to avoid any pain or
unpleasant truths, and in doing so
maintain a comfortable distance.
What you call friendship is overwhelmingly\na thing of convenience—nothing more.
But those lovely friends of yours carry\nsecrets nonetheless. Isn't that right, Elly?
Cram it with walnuts, lady! There ain't no\nway Elisanne's keepin' secrets from us.
Luca is correct. Elisanne would never...\nEr, Elisanne?
Focus, everyone. Ciella would say\nanything to try and tear us apart.
Yeah, the boss is onto ya, lady—so stop\ntryin' to mess with our heads already!

He warned me not to lay a hand on any
of you, but it seems I am left with little
choice—so perhaps just a small bit
of playtime is in order...

We are Agito. We are wings of judgment
which unfurl in rejection of the deceit of
this world! Awash in your nonsense, you
shall learn of truth and despair from ME!
